function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> isuppercase(first(word)), words)
end
```
This function uses the `filter` function to iterate over the input list of words and keeps only the words for which the condition `isuppercase(first(word))` is true. The `isuppercase` function checks if the first character of the word is uppercase, and the `first` function returns the first character of the string.
